</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 7:31:56 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Odd question but...</span><hr size=1> They'd put another method in the game to get to those planes.  I think they wouuld be concerned and work on Wizards more but they wouldn't just rely on Wizards to get to the planes.<br>
<br>
I think the original idea was to help balance the late-beta gutted Wizard class by adding ports and sight spells.  They gave Wizards the planar gates, because they saw what we all know: Druids have ports too and are better balanced and have a zillion abilities to solo and group well.  But then they freaked out, terrified Wizards would exploit this and make money at the gates, so they added highly expensive gems required to port up.  That wasn't enough of a limitation, people STILL required a Wizard to go up there, so they removed one plane from our porting ability, and from that point on all planes released have been walk ons.<br>
<br>
Since GZ admitted the sight spells didn't really help us, we have two problems with Verant's version of the balanced Wizard (remember, this is on THEIR terms, not ours):<br>
<br>
Ports don't balance us because Druids are better built for soloing and grouping<br>
Planar gates don't balance us because they only go to 2 of the 5 present planes (and I highly doubt Bertox's plane will require a spell)<br>
Sight spells don't balance us because they don't DO anything, the only two useful ones had one huge nerf and the other is nearly worthless as a sight spell.<br>
<br>
So Verants attempt to fix the class after hacking its guts out in Beta resulted in a total flop and only recently have they begun to admit this.  After its too late, having made the imbalance more grossly clear by overpowering melee. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utanstaafl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanstaafl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 7:44:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Odd question but...</span><hr size=1> Sadly I think not much would happen Graffe.<br>
<br>
We fill a void that simply doesn't exist.  There are almost no scenrios in the game where fast spell damage is better than fast melee damage.  <br>
<br>
Melee damage and healing - Thats the very core of what EQ combat is about.  We can't heal or melee, nor can we make others better at healing or melee.  Therefore when looked at at it most basic level we are superfulous where EQ combat is concerned. Or put another way, we fill a non existant void. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uquikpick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quikpick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 8:31:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Odd question but...</span><hr size=1> I don't think Verant would add another method of getting to Air and Hate in the game. It would require everyone to download that whole zone map again. And as Verant stated before this is why our portal in WK will never be moved. Then again they could always contradict themselves and maybe put a portal somewhere like the spectre island in Oasis.<br>
<br>
It is sad to see so few wizzies around any more. People are always scrounging around for us to gate them to the planes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvespid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vespid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 8:50:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Odd question but...</span><hr size=1> They'd just add a new item for tanks with the effect Alter Plane: Hate, no regeant required.<br>
<br>
Hopefully it would be an Uber 1hs that proc'd it though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p><img src="http://ns.iicanada.com/scott/pimp.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/useverinewolfe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Severine Wolfe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 9:06:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.clan-donald.com/screenshots/severine.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Odd question but...</span><hr size=1> Honestly?  I think they would just make Hate and Sky walk on like they did Fear.<br>
